==English==
===Adjective===
'''mutually intelligible'''

# {{linguistics}} Of a speech variety, able to be understood by speakers of another variety.
#*'''1992,''' Jørgen Rischel, ''Language Contact: Theoretical and Empirical Studies''
#*:Hmong consists of some very distinct dialects which, however, are reported to be '''mutually intelligible'''.
#*'''2005,''' Robert L. Rankin, ''Native Languages Of The Southeastern United States''
#*:The Kansa (Kaw) tribe lived in northeastern Kansas, and their language was '''mutually intelligible''' with that of the Osages, who lived mostly in southwestern Missouri and adjacent areas.
